{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require NHS to offer base line X-rays for children born with a limb difference",
        "additional_details": "When a limb different child attends A&E following an injury, some doctors cannot tell what is normal anatomy for that child and what is a new injury. Without a baseline X-ray on NHS records, there is risk of misdiagnosis, missed fractures and incorrect treatment. families are left having to answer medical questions in moments of crisis. One single baseline X-ray taken at diagnosis, stored and accessible to any emergency team nationwide, changes everything.",
        "background": "Limb different children have unusual anatomy. Without a baseline X-ray on NHS records, some A&E doctors can\u2019t tell what is an injury & what is the norm for that child. We want every limb different child to have a baseline X-ray at diagnosis, stored and easily accessible",
